	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>DRW</b> [ Fri Feb 17, 2017 3:54 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Are famiclones illegal?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Unless the console actually has the name Nintendo or any registered trademarks on it and as long as the console doesn't come with copyrighted software (i.e. a multi-cartridge with actual games by Nintendo or their third party publishers), you should be fine.<br /><br />If it wasn't legal, I doubt RetroUSB would get away with this:<br /><!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=36&amp;products_id=78">www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath ... ucts_id=78</a><!-- w -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Fri Feb 17, 2017 3:57 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Are famiclones illegal?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Famicom was only ever protected by patent law.<br />The Famicom predates <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semiconductor_Chip_Protection_Act_of_1984" class="postlink">mask protections</a>.<br />The NES's CIC was additionally protected by copyright law.<br />Random bits (logo, shape) are protected by trademark and/or <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trade_dress" class="postlink">trade dress</a> law.<br />Individual games are protected by copyright law.<br /><br />There's nothing about a bare famiclone that should infringe, in any way.<br /><br />Now, if it's one of those ones that come with N games built in, sure, the games infringe copyright.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Dwedit</b> [ Fri Feb 17, 2017 4:47 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Are famiclones illegal?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The clone systems themselves are fine, but you'll almost never see them without pirated games.<br />The only exception I've seen is when they got bundled with original games, including graphical hacks of Somari that removed any traces or Sonic or Mario from the games.<br /><br />You now have &quot;onebus&quot; versions, which have a flash chip on there too, with pre-burned games.  There's integrated CHR-RAM and integrated MMC3.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


