	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nintendo has gone after shops offering famiclones.  I saw this happen at a local mall years ago.<br /><br />The Coleco Gemini is an example of a perfectly legal system clone (Atari 2600) that still had to deal with litigation and settlement.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nytimes.com/1982/12/09/business/coleco-industries-is-sued-by-atari.html">http://www.nytimes.com/1982/12/09/busin ... atari.html</a><!-- m --><br /><br />So, yeah.  You can make compatible hardware.  The real trouble started when companies started embedding IP into their devices via firmware/BIOs.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
